                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/841h: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-06">June 6,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>594. Reference Department’s 583, June 4. Since <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    after departure from Lisbon will proceed another port for embarkation additional
                    American evacuees estimated at 800, aliens additional to those already
                    specifically authorized by Department should not be embarked at Bordeaux. Lisbon
                    reports expects approximately 100 Americans for embarkation there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
